    WELCOME TO MY SOURCE!
     
    Hey, isn’t this the best indented source you’ve ever seen?
    And it’s HTML5—so it must be awesome.
     
    If you want to see the “real” source of this website, check out:
    https://github.com/hagenburger/hagenburger
    (And don’t forget to watch the project and to follow me there ^^)
     
  %head
    %meta(charset="utf-8")
    - if current_page.data.description
      %meta(name="description" content="#{current_page.data.description}")
    - if current_page.data.keywords
      %meta(name="keywords" content="#{current_page.data.keywords}")
    %meta(name="date" content="#{(@date || Time.now).strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    %meta(property="og:site_name" content="hagenburger.net")
    %meta(property="og:title" content="#{current_page.data.og_title || current_page.data.title}")
    %meta(property="og:image" content="#{current_page.data.og_image || asset_url('hagenburger.jpg')}")
    %title&= [current_page.data.title, ('Nico Hagenburger' if current_page.data.title.length < 45)].compact.join(' ··· ').strip
    %link(rel="apple-touch-icon" href="#{asset_url('apple-touch-icon.png')}")
    %link(rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" href="#{asset_url('hagenburger.rss')}")
    %link(rel="stylesheet" href="#{asset_url('stylesheets/hagenburger.css?2')}")
    - if css = @css || yield_content(:css)
      %style(type="text/css")= css
    %script(src="//use.typekit.com/fal4qpz.js" async onload="try{Typekit.load()}catch(e){}")
    - if @stylesheet
      %link(rel="stylesheet" href="#{asset_url("stylesheets/#{@stylesheet}.css")}")
    - javascript = @jquery || @javascript || yield_content(:javascript)
    %script for(var e,l='article aside figcaption figure footer header nav section time'.split(' ');e=l.pop();document.createElement(e));try{Typekit.load()}catch(e){};document.getElementsByTagName('HTML')[0].className+=' js'
  %body
    #nico-hagenburger
      %header
        %a(href="/")
          %img#logo(src="#{asset_url('images/nico-hagenburger-ruby-on-rails.png')}" alt="Nico Hagenburger — #{(@keywords || [] + ['Ruby on Rails', 'Haml', 'Sass', 'HTML5'])[0..6].join(', ')}")
        %nav<
          = link_to 'Home', '/'
          = link_to 'Blog', '/BLOG.html'
          = link_to 'Contact', '/CONTACT.html'
          = link_to 'Portfolio', '/PORTFOLIO.html'
        %div<
          %strong> Hi, I’m Nico Hagenburger
          %br>
          I enjoy designing
          %br>
          clean, simple websites
          %br>
          and developing web applications in Ruby on Rails.
      #content
        - if request.path =~ %r(BLOG/)
          %article.post{ :slug => @slug }
            = yield
            = facebook_like
          = partial 'twitter'
        - else
          = yield
    %footer
      %a#github(href="https://github.com/hagenburger")
        %span Fork me on GitHub!
        %span Get free lemonade!
      %small<
        © Nico Hagenburger/Hagenburger GmbH 2000—#{Time.now.year} · Blog posts published under CC share alike licence (except design and artwork or otherwise mentioned)
    = javascript_include_tag 'hagenburger'
  /
